PARLUX,  FROM  7<ql>
<m0>Smaller brands ``always have a following,'' he said. And ``companies like Parlux are really bottom fishers.''<ep>
   In January, Parlux announced the purchase of Richard Barrie Fragrances, including a manufacturing and distribution center in Orange, Conn., and the Baryshnikov and Melrose Place fragrances.<ep>
   In an SEC filing Apr. 22, Richard Barrie said that as of last December, the company had a negative net worth of $14,244.<ep>
   The Richard Barrie acquisition will give Parlux a manufacturing facility and ``help them to save some cost and give them more control over their product,'' said Pope.<ep>
   Parlux said it buys its bottles and other supplies in the United States and abroad and fills them primarily in New Jersey and Connecticut.<ep>
    ``They're shrewd businessmen,'' Mottus said. ``They understand the movement and traffic of cosmetic brands.''<ep>
     Parlux's rivals are active, too.<ep>
     Miami-based French Fragrances, whose shelves include Halston and Geoffrey Beene fragrances, recently announced an agreement to buy several other prestigious brands.<ep>
   ``We are good competitors,'' said company president Rafael Kravec. ``We know them well.''<ql>
